The main objective of this project is to design and develop a smart autonomous robotic 
car based on an Arduino embedded system. The goal is to demonstrate the effective 
integration of hardware and software components to enable both manual and autonomous 
operation of the vehicle. 
The specific objectives of this project include: 
• Designing and assembling a four-wheel-drive (4WD) robotic platform using 
appropriate mechanical and electronic components.  
• Implementing a reliable control system based on an Arduino microcontroller to 
ensure real-time data processing and decision-making.  
• Developing a Bluetooth-based wireless communication interface to allow user control 
of the robot via a mobile application.  
• Integrating an ultrasonic sensor to detect and avoid obstacles, enabling safe 
navigation in dynamic environments.  
• Implementing a line-following mechanism using infrared (IR) sensors for accurate 
path tracking and autonomous movement.  
• Developing and optimizing embedded software using the Arduino IDE for efficient 
sensor data processing and motor control.  
• Evaluating system performance in terms of accuracy, responsiveness, and reliability 
under various operating conditions.  
• Designing a modular and scalable architecture that can be extended with advanced 
technologies such as artificial intelligence, computer vision, and Internet of Things 
(IoT) in future enhancements.  
Through these objectives, the project seeks to provide a solid understanding of robotics, 
embedded systems, and intelligent control, while showcasing practical applications in 
automation and smart mobility. 
